# Secure Password Manager 🔒

A command-line password manager built with Python that securely stores and encrypts passwords using AES-256 encryption.

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.x-blue)
![Cryptography](https://img.shields.io/badge/Cryptography-Fernet-green)

## Features ✨

- 🔐 Master password protection
- 🛡️ AES-256 encryption via Fernet
- 🧂 Unique salt per user for key derivation
- 📁 Encrypted password storage
- ➕ Add, view, and manage passwords
- 🚫 No plaintext passwords stored

## Installation ⚙️

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/secure-password-manager.git
   cd secure-password-manager
